data.title: 1960 LOTUS MODEL 18 FORMULA JUNIOR available for Auction
data.meta_description: This 1960 Lotus Model 18 Formula Junior is an open-wheel racecar that has competed on tracks across North America. It was restored in 2000 under the direction of a vintage racecar specialty facility and features a wraparound windshield, wobbly-web wheels, a tubular roll bar, and RaceQuip safety harnesses. Power is provided by a rebuilt Cosworth Ford 105E 1100cc four-cylinder mated to a rebuilt Hewland six-speed manual transaxle. Finished in two-tone green and yellow and equipped with a red vinyl bucket seat, this Model 18 is now offered by the selling dealer with documentation, receipts, a dyno sheet, spare parts, the removed original Renault gearbox, and a bill of sale.
data.text:
Enter the dollar amount you’re willing to pay for the vehicle in the bidding box. Type in the amount you’d like to bid and click “submit bid.” If your bid does not meet the minimum requirement for the vehicle, you will see an error message telling you the lowest amount you can enter to bid.

If you are the highest bidder, you will see a notification stating so, and if you are outbid you will be notified on the screen and via email. If you wish to continue bidding, you must enter your new amount into the bidding box. You can also click on “bid history” to see all bids on the vehicle.
